    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>In a UnitTest an (invoice) row object is begin created and deleted shortly after that.</p>

<p>$invoiceobj = new Invoice();
$invoice = $invoiceobj-&gt;createRow($data);
$invoice-&gt;save();
...
$invoice-&gt;delete();</p>

<p>This however does not work - the resulting query:
DELETE FROM <code>invoices</code> WHERE (id = '<code>invoices</code>.<code>id</code> = 21');
does not delete the line.</p>

<p>The workaround:
$object-&gt;getTable()-&gt;delete($object-&gt;id);
works well - the row is being removed.</p>

